# Cluster-first

GastroLog has no primary node. Any node may serve any request. If a design only works when the client hits a specific node, it is wrong. Before shipping: *Does this work if the user is on a different node than the data?*

# Local dev: prefer Unix sockets

For local processes (`just cluster-run`, dev cluster):

- Prefer **`gastrolog` CLI without `--addr`** (and without a token) so it dials **`gastrolog.sock`** under the node **`--home`**. Using `--addr http://localhost:…` disables the socket path and forces TCP + JWT (`--token` / `GASTROLOG_TOKEN`) unless you intentionally test HTTP.
- Target a node: `gastrolog --home <path-to-node-home> …`, or `--addr unix://<absolute>/gastrolog.sock`.
- Keep node state under repo **`data/node{N}`** (or another gitignored dir). Align **`GLOG_DATA_DIR`** / **`scripts/cluster.sh --data-dir`**. `backend/justfile` **`cluster-kill`** assumes **`data/node*`**.

# Local admin credentials (HTTP/JWT)

Root and `backend/` **justfiles** use **`set dotenv-load`**; repo **`.env`** supplies **`GLOG_ADMIN_USER`** / **`GLOG_ADMIN_PASS`**. Scripts default to `admin` / `admin123` only when those vars are unset. For Login/curl failures, use `.env` or `"$GLOG_ADMIN_USER"` / `"$GLOG_ADMIN_PASS"` after `source .env` — never paste secrets into chat or commits.

# Cursor embedded browser vs real browser

The embedded browser tab can degrade (RPCs hang though the server is fine). If **curl** and **Chrome** work, mention closing/reopening the embedded tab as a *secondary* hypothesis before blaming Vite or the cluster.

# curl against Vite

Use **`http://localhost:<port>`**, not **`http://127.0.0.1:<port>`**, so the host matches Vite **`server.host`** (often `localhost` / `::1`).
